Moe's BBQ has made for the worst possible neighbor to the people who live in the apartment building across the street. Instead of giving you a buzzer or having someone bring your order to your table, they announce orders over a loud speaker both inside and outside the restaurant. The outside loud speaker can literally be heard for blocks around. Why it needs to be that loud beats me, but needless to say it’s really annoying for the people who live across the street to have to constantly hear "Johnny, your order is ready" throughout the evening. Their outdoor patio is empty now that the weather has turned colder, but the loud speaker announcements are still blaring away all the same. To make matters worse, they have also begun leaving their outdoor music running all night long, in clear violation of Huntsville's noise ordinance.  I’ve reached out to the general manager at Moe’s about it and they could not care less. Half the time they just hang up on you, while the other half they agree but do nothing. If you go over there in person and ask to talk to a manager, they’ll tell you that he/she is busy and you should come back another time, or that they’ll “pass on the message”.  So in short, don't support this business until they become a better neighbor.

4 Stars for excellent food and -1 for parking :-)  Moe's BBQ is probably my favorite BBQ place in the North Alabama area.  Everything I have ever had here is amazing.  My number one choice is the smoked wings, with my second choice being their catfish.  I would also say Moe's might have the best hush puppies I've ever had.  I am very surprised to see some reviews regarding cold or not good food.  This really does surprise me as I have eaten at many Moe's and they have always been great IMO.   This location is so so to me and that is my opinion.  I am not big on the Downtown area mainly due to the annoyance of parking and having to walk to where you want to go.  There are very limited spots near Moe's and DO NOT park in the Apartment parking lot behind or you will be towed.  With that being said, this location is very cool and I would highly recommend at least trying it out.   When fall hits I want to go enjoy dinner on the roof.
